<i>noun</i>: 화색 [화색], 화기 [화기], 혈색 [혈쌕], 핏기 [피끼/핃끼], 불빛 [불삗] <i>verb</i>: 후끈후끈하다 [후끈후끈하다], 후끈하다 [후끈하다], 후끈대다 [후끈대다], 후끈거리다 [후끈거리다], 화끈화끈하다 [화끈화끈하다], 화끈하다 [화끈하다], 화끈대다 [화끈대다], 화끈거리다 [화끈거리다], 피어나다 [피어나다/피여나다], 상기되다 [상ː기되다/상ː기뒈다], 빛나다 [빈나다], 달아오르다 [다라오르다] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>화색 [화색]</dt><br>
<dd>glow; radiance</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴에 드러나는 부드럽고 환한 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A mild and bright look appearing on one's face.</dd><br>
<dt>화기 [화기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. warm temperature</dd><br>
<dd>따뜻하고 화창한 기온.</dd><br>
<dd>The warm temperature on a sunny day.</dd><br>
<dd>2. geniality; amicability; harmony</dd><br>
<dd>온화한 얼굴빛. 또는 화목한 분위기.</dd><br>
<dd>Mild countenance or harmonious atmosphere.</dd><br>
<dd>3. glow; radiance; luster</dd><br>
<dd>밝고 건강한 얼굴빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A bright and healthy look appearing on one's face.</dd><br>
<dt>혈색 [혈쌕]</dt><br>
<dd>1. glow; luster; color; radiance</dd><br>
<dd>살갗에 보이는 핏기.</dd><br>
<dd>A glow with a tinge of red on one's complexion.</dd><br>
<dd>2. blood red; crimson</dd><br>
<dd>피처럼 새빨간 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A scarlet red color like that of blood.</dd><br>
<dt>핏기 [피끼/핃끼]</dt><br>
<dd>glow; luster; color; radiance</dd><br>
<dd>사람의 피부에 보이는 불그스레한 피의 기운.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of glowing with a tinge of red on one's complexion.</dd><br>
<dt>불빛 [불삗]</dt><br>
<dd>1. firelight; glow</dd><br>
<dd>타오르는 불의 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A light of burning fire.</dd><br>
<dd>2. light; beam</dd><br>
<dd>켜 놓은 불에서 나오는 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A ray emitted from a light that is turned on.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt>후끈후끈하다 [후끈후끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot or for one's face to suddenly feel hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt>후끈하다 [후끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to become hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt>후끈대다 [후끈대다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to feel hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt>후끈거리다 [후끈거리다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to feel hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt>화끈화끈하다 [화끈화끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot, being exposed to heat or for one's face to become suddenly hot and turn red, or to feel a surge of heat.</dd><br>
<dt>화끈하다 [화끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to become hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt>화끈대다 [화끈대다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot, being exposed to heat or for one's face to become suddenly hot and turn red, or to feel a surge of heat.</dd><br>
<dt>화끈거리다 [화끈거리다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot, being exposed to heat or for one's face to become suddenly hot and turn red, or to feel a surge of heat.</dd><br>
<dt>피어나다 [피어나다/피여나다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. bloom; come out</dd><br>
<dd>꽃 등이 피게 되다.</dd><br>
<dd>For a flower, etc., to come into bloom.</dd><br>
<dd>2. burn; kindle</dd><br>
<dd>불이나 연기 등이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For fire or smoke, etc., to rise.</dd><br>
<dd>3. bloom; glow</dd><br>
<dd>기운이 활발해지거나 좋아지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For one's vitality to become strong or to return.</dd><br>
<dd>4. rise; go up; trail</dd><br>
<dd>냄새나 먼지 등이 일어나 퍼지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For a smell or dust, etc., to rise and spread.</dd><br>
<dd>5. rise; come up; well up</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 느낌이나 생각 등이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For a certain feeling or thought, etc., to rise.</dd><br>
<dd>6. bloom; appear</dd><br>
<dd>웃음이나 미소 등이 얼굴이나 입가에 드러나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For laughter or smile, etc., to appear on the face or lips.</dd><br>
<dt>상기되다 [상ː기되다/상ː기뒈다]</dt><br>
<dd>flush; glow</dd><br>
<dd>흥분하거나 부끄러워 얼굴이 붉어지다.</dd><br>
<dd>To blush because one is excited or embarrassed.</dd><br>
<dt>빛나다 [빈나다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. shine</dd><br>
<dd>빛이 환히 비치다.</dd><br>
<dd>For light to shine brightly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. twinkle; glow</dd><br>
<dd>빛이 반사되어 반짝거리거나 윤이 나다.</dd><br>
<dd>To be shiny or glossy when light is reflected.</dd><br>
<dd>3. look better</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 것이 매우 돋보이거나 가치 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>For something to look better or to be valuable.</dd><br>
<dd>4. shine; glow</dd><br>
<dd>눈이 맑은 빛을 띠다.</dd><br>
<dd>For one's eyes to look clear.</dd><br>
<dt>달아오르다 [다라오르다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. burn; become hot</dd><br>
<dd>물체가 매우 뜨거워지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become extremely hot.</dd><br>
<dd>2. glow</dd><br>
<dd>얼굴이 뜨거워 빨갛게 되다.</dd><br>
<dd>For one's face to get hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dd>3. burn; get hot</dd><br>
<dd>몸이나 마음에 열이 오르다.</dd><br>
<dd>For one's body or mind to get hot.</dd><br>
<dd>4. be stimulated</dd><br>
<dd>분위기나 기운, 상태 등이 왕성하게 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For a mood, energy, state, etc., to become active.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>